<SysML:Requirement id="2f34d408-81b5-11f1-a40e-f0c5d781d7c8">
<externalId>
<val>03</val>
</externalId>
<name>
<val>Hygienic Disposal</val>
</name>
<owningPackage>
<ref refid="012edaba-70f5-11ec-aabc-f47b099bf663"/>
</owningPackage>
<package>
<ref refid="012edaba-70f5-11ec-aabc-f47b099bf663"/>
</package>
<presentation>
<reflist>
<ref refid="2f3526a4-81b5-11f1-a018-f0c5d781d7c8"/>
<ref refid="8e230f7e-81bb-11f1-8406-f0c5d781d7c8"/>
</reflist>
</presentation>
<text>
<val>The system shall consolidate all captured insects into a single, centralized containment area to simplify cleaning and ensure completely hands-off disposal.</val>
</text>
</SysML:Requirement>
<SysML:RequirementItem id="2f3526a4-81b5-11f1-a018-f0c5d781d7c8">
<matrix>
<val>(1.0, 0.0, 0.0, 1.0, 749.0, 222.0)</val>
</matrix>
<top-left>
<val>(4.0, 0.0)</val>
</top-left>
<width>
<val>238.0</val>
</width>
<height>
<val>176.0</val>
</height>
<diagram>
<ref refid="01a97fa8-70f6-11ec-aabc-f47b099bf663"/>
</diagram>
<subject>
<ref refid="2f34d408-81b5-11f1-a40e-f0c5d781d7c8"/>
</subject>
</SysML:RequirementItem>
<SysML:Requirement id="bf104323-81b5-11f1-98cf-f0c5d781d7c8">
<externalId>
<val>LR-01</val>
</externalId>
<name>
<val>Dual-Entry, Single-Containment Design</val>
</name>
<owningPackage>
<ref refid="cca1054c-70f5-11ec-aabc-f47b099bf663"/>
</owningPackage>
<package>
<ref refid="cca1054c-70f5-11ec-aabc-f47b099bf663"/>
</package>
<presentation>
<reflist>
<ref refid="bf109dc3-81b5-11f1-b76b-f0c5d781d7c8"/>
<ref refid="d948b954-8348-11f1-8e2c-f0c5d781d7c8"/>
</reflist>
</presentation>
<targetDirectedRelationshipPropertyPath_>
<reflist>
<ref refid="00d9cec3-81bc-11f1-a01d-f0c5d781d7c8"/>
</reflist>
</targetDirectedRelationshipPropertyPath_>
<text>
<val>The system shall feature separate entry channels and distinct attraction mechanisms optimized for crawling insects versus flying insects, both routing into a single, shared elimination area.</val>
</text>
</SysML:Requirement>
<SysML:RequirementItem id="bf109dc3-81b5-11f1-b76b-f0c5d781d7c8">
<matrix>
<val>(1.0, 0.0, 0.0, 1.0, 150.0, 209.0)</val>
</matrix>
<top-left>
<val>(0.0, 0.0)</val>
</top-left>
<width>
<val>234.0</val>
</width>
<height>
<val>212.0</val>
</height>
<diagram>
<ref refid="07658ade-70f8-11ec-aabc-f47b099bf663"/>
</diagram>
<subject>
<ref refid="bf104323-81b5-11f1-98cf-f0c5d781d7c8"/>
</subject>
</SysML:RequirementItem>
<SysML:Requirement id="db21b353-81b5-11f1-8847-f0c5d781d7c8">
<externalId>
<val>LR-02</val>
</externalId>
<name>
<val>Multi-Directional One-Way Ingress</val>
</name>
<owningPackage>
<ref refid="cca1054c-70f5-11ec-aabc-f47b099bf663"/>
</owningPackage>
<package>
<ref refid="cca1054c-70f5-11ec-aabc-f47b099bf663"/>
</package>
<presentation>
<reflist>
<ref refid="db21ee1a-81b5-11f1-b810-f0c5d781d7c8"/>
<ref refid="fc58099c-8348-11f1-bf68-f0c5d781d7c8"/>
</reflist>
</presentation>
<targetDirectedRelationshipPropertyPath_>
<reflist>
<ref refid="26f5daad-81bc-11f1-8816-f0c5d781d7c8"/>
</reflist>
</targetDirectedRelationshipPropertyPath_>
<text>
<val>The trapping mechanisms shall allow one-way mechanical or physical entry from both the crawling and flying input streams into the shared containment area while blocking any return path.</val>
</text>
</SysML:Requirement>
<SysML:RequirementItem id="db21ee1a-81b5-11f1-b810-f0c5d781d7c8">
<matrix>
<val>(1.0, 0.0, 0.0, 1.0, 472.2222222222223, 209.0)</val>
</matrix>
<top-left>
<val>(0.0, 0.0)</val>
</top-left>
<width>
<val>240.6111111111112</val>
</width>
<height>
<val>212.0</val>
</height>
<diagram>
<ref refid="07658ade-70f8-11ec-aabc-f47b099bf663"/>
</diagram>
<subject>
<ref refid="db21b353-81b5-11f1-8847-f0c5d781d7c8"/>
</subject>
</SysML:RequirementItem>
<SysML:Requirement id="f5244593-81b5-11f1-a847-f0c5d781d7c8">
<externalId>
<val>LR-03</val>
</externalId>
<name>
<val>Convergent Flow Management</val>
</name>
<owningPackage>
<ref refid="cca1054c-70f5-11ec-aabc-f47b099bf663"/>
</owningPackage>
<package>
<ref refid="cca1054c-70f5-11ec-aabc-f47b099bf663"/>
</package>
<presentation>
<reflist>
<ref refid="f524913a-81b5-11f1-89f7-f0c5d781d7c8"/>
<ref refid="d5048007-8348-11f1-8dca-f0c5d781d7c8"/>
</reflist>
</presentation>
<targetDirectedRelationshipPropertyPath_>
<reflist>
<ref refid="3badc232-81bc-11f1-bb24-f0c5d781d7c8"/>
</reflist>
</targetDirectedRelationshipPropertyPath_>
<text>
<val>The internal system logic shall manage internal environmental triggers (e.g., airflow currents, gravity transitions) to successfully guide both crawling and flying pests toward the common elimination zone.</val>
</text>
</SysML:Requirement>
<SysML:RequirementItem id="f524913a-81b5-11f1-89f7-f0c5d781d7c8">
<matrix>
<val>(1.0, 0.0, 0.0, 1.0, 818.0, 209.0)</val>
</matrix>
<top-left>
<val>(0.0, 0.0)</val>
</top-left>
<width>
<val>249.0</val>
</width>
<height>
<val>194.0</val>
</height>
<diagram>
<ref refid="07658ade-70f8-11ec-aabc-f47b099bf663"/>
</diagram>
<subject>
<ref refid="f5244593-81b5-11f1-a847-f0c5d781d7c8"/>
</subject>
</SysML:RequirementItem>
<SysML:Requirement id="2f04341e-81b6-11f1-8e5c-f0c5d781d7c8">
<externalId>
<val>PR-01</val>
</externalId>
<name>
<val>Unified Removable Collection Reservoir</val>
</name>
<owningPackage>
<ref refid="274478f2-70f7-11ec-aabc-f47b099bf663"/>
</owningPackage>
<package>
<ref refid="274478f2-70f7-11ec-aabc-f47b099bf663"/>
</package>
<presentation>
<reflist>
<ref refid="2f04826e-81b6-11f1-8615-f0c5d781d7c8"/>
</reflist>
</presentation>
<targetDirectedRelationshipPropertyPath_>
<reflist>
<ref refid="ec1b98f4-8348-11f1-9fd8-f0c5d781d7c8"/>
</reflist>
</targetDirectedRelationshipPropertyPath_>
<text>
<val>The bottom section of the chassis shall house a single, unified, detachable drawer mechanism that serves as the shared trapping and killing zone for all insect types.</val>
</text>
</SysML:Requirement>
<SysML:RequirementItem id="2f04826e-81b6-11f1-8615-f0c5d781d7c8">
<matrix>
<val>(1.0, 0.0, 0.0, 1.0, 90.0, 177.0)</val>
</matrix>
<top-left>
<val>(0.0, 0.0)</val>
</top-left>
<width>
<val>236.0</val>
</width>
<height>
<val>194.0</val>
</height>
<diagram>
<ref refid="b2a178f0-70f7-11ec-aabc-f47b099bf663"/>
</diagram>
<subject>
<ref refid="2f04341e-81b6-11f1-8e5c-f0c5d781d7c8"/>
</subject>
</SysML:RequirementItem>
<SysML:Requirement id="4b8c70af-81b6-11f1-bd1c-f0c5d781d7c8">
<externalId>
<val>PR-02</val>
</externalId>
<name>
<val>Crawling &amp; Flying Guide Funnels</val>
</name>
<owningPackage>
<ref refid="274478f2-70f7-11ec-aabc-f47b099bf663"/>
</owningPackage>
<package>
<ref refid="274478f2-70f7-11ec-aabc-f47b099bf663"/>
</package>
<presentation>
<reflist>
<ref refid="4b8cadfb-81b6-11f1-a965-f0c5d781d7c8"/>
</reflist>
</presentation>
<targetDirectedRelationshipPropertyPath_>
<reflist>
<ref refid="10456e3f-8349-11f1-8208-f0c5d781d7c8"/>
</reflist>
</targetDirectedRelationshipPropertyPath_>
<text>
<val>The physical chassis structure shall include a smooth, steep internal funnel (for flying insects caught via fan suction) and targeted lower entry tracks (for crawling insects) that both dump directly into the common reservoir.</val>
</text>
</SysML:Requirement>
<SysML:RequirementItem id="4b8cadfb-81b6-11f1-a965-f0c5d781d7c8">
